cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of shared autonomy in controlling a quadrotor and a video game. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning framework for shared autonomy. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses neural network function approximation for learning the end-to-end mapping. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of human-in-the-loop reinforcement learning and controlled studies with users. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of semi-autonomous control in achieving a common goal.
